                    <h3>Environmental Impact:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span>Toxic Chemicals:</span> Electronic waste contains hazardous materials like lead, mercury, and cadmium that can leach into the soil and water when not disposed of properly.</li>
                        <li><span>Non-Biodegradable:</span> Most electronics don't break down in landfills, contributing to pollution and environmental degradation.</li>
                        <li><span>E-Waste Problem:</span> The amount of e-waste is rapidly increasing due to the fast pace of technology upgrades, and it's expected to grow exponentially in the coming years.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
